Electro electrofunk genre electronic music and early hip hop directly influenced the use the Roland TR808 drum machines and funk Records the genre typically feature drum machines and heavy electronic sounds usually without vocals although vocals are present they are delivered deadpan manner often through electronic distortion such vocoding and talkboxing This the main distinction between electro and previously prominent genres such disco which the electronic sound was only part the instrumentation also palpably deviates from its predecessor boogie for being less vocaloriented and more focused electronic beats produced drum machines Following the decline disco music the United States electro emerged fusion funk and New York boogie Early hip hop and rap combined with German and Japanese electropop influences such Kraftwerk and Yellow Magic Orchestra YMO inspired the birth electro 1982 producer Arthur Baker with Afrika Bambaataa released the seminal Planet Rock which was built using samples from Kraftwerks Trans Europe Express and drum beats supplied the TR808 Planet Rock was followed later that year another breakthrough electro record Nunk Warp 1983 Hashim created electro funk sound which influenced Herbie Hancock resulting his hit single Rockit The early 1980s were electros mainstream peak the mid 1980s the genre moved away from its electronic and funk influences using harder edged beats and rock samples exemplified Run DMC Electro became popular again the late 1990s with artists such Anthony Rother and DJs such Dave Clarke third wave popularity occurred 2007 Electro has branched out into subgenres including Electrocore and Skweee which developed Sweden and Finland From its inception one the defining characteristics the electro sound was the use drum machines particularly the Roland TR808 the rhythmic basis the track the genre evolved computers and sampling replaced drum machines electronic music and are now used the majority electro producers important note that although the electro the 1980s and contemporary electro electronic dance music both grew out the dissolution disco they are now different genres Classic 1980s electro drum patterns tend electronic emulations breakbeats occasionally four the floor pattern used well with syncopated kick drum and usually snare clap accenting the backbeat The difference between electro drumbeats and breakbeats breaks that electro tends more mechanical while breakbeats tend have more humanlike feel like that live drummer The definition however somewhat ambiguous nature due the various uses the term The Roland TR808 drum machine hit the market 1980 defining early electro with its immediately recognizable sound Staccato percussive drumbeats tended dominate electro almost exclusively provided the TR808 inexpensive way producing drum sound the TR808 caught quickly with the producers early electro because the ability its bass drum generate extreme lowfrequencies This aspect the Roland TR808 was especially appealing producers who would test drive their tracks nightclubs like NYCs Funhouse where the bass drum sound was essential for records success Its unique percussion sounds like handclaps open and closed highhat clave and cowbell became integral the electro sound number popular songs the early 1980s employed the TR808 including Marvin Gayes Sexual Healing Cybotrons Clear and Afrika Bambaataas Planet Rock The Roland TR808 has attained iconic status eventually being used more hits than any other drum machine Through the use samples the Roland TR808 remains popular electro and other genres the present day Other electro instrumentation was generally electronic favoring analog synthesis programmed bass lines sequenced arpeggiated synthetic riffs and atonal sound effects all created with synthesizers Heavy use effects such reverbs delays chorus phasers along with eerie synthetic ensemble strings pad sounds emphasized the science fiction futuristic themes classic 1980s electro represented the lyrics andor music Electro hip hop group Warp 1983 single Light Years Away produced and written Lotti Golden and Richard Scher exemplifies the SciFi afrofuturist aspect electro reflected both the lyrics and instrumentation The imagery its lyrical refrain space the place for the human race pays homage Sun Ras 1974 film while its synth lines and sound effects are informed scifi computer games and cartoonsborn sciencefiction revival Most electro instrumental but common element vocals processed through vocoder Additionally speech synthesis may used create robotic mechanical lyrical content the iconic Planet Rock and the automatous chant the chorus Nunk Warp Although primarily instrumental early electro utilized rap Male rap dominated the genre however female rappers are integral part the electro tradition whether featured group Warp solo performers like Roxanne Shante The lyrical style that emerged along with electro became less popular the 1990s rapping continued evolve becoming the domain hip hop music About electro origins Greg Wilson claims Following the decline disco music the late 1970s various funk artists such Zapp Roger began experimenting with talk boxes and the use heavier more distinctive beats Boogie played role during the formative years electro notably Feels Good Electra Emergency EMDS6527 the postdisco production Youre the One for Train Prelude PRL 621 and the Eric MatthewDarryl Payne productions Thanks You Sinnamon Becket BKD 508 and Journey Sing The Funk Electric Electrik Funk Prelude PRL 541 Electro eventually emerged fusion different styles including funk boogie combined with German and Japanese technopop addition influences from the futurism Alvin Toffler martial arts films and video game music The genres immediate forebearers included Kraftwerk Yellow Magic Orchestra YMO and Cat Stevens 1980 YMO was the first band utilize the TR808 programmable drum machine That same year YMO member Ryuichi Sakamoto released Riot Lagos which regarded early example electro 